properties.description: The following arguments are supported:

properties.name: project
properties.description: • project - (Required) The id of the project.

properties.name: branch
properties.description: • branch - (Required) Name of the branch.

properties.name: push_access_level
properties.description: • push_access_level - (Required) One of five levels of access to the project.

properties.name: merge_access_level
properties.description: • merge_access_level - (Required) One of five levels of access to the project.
The following arguments are supported:

properties.name: project
properties.description: • project - (Required, string) The name or id of the project to add the deploy key to.

properties.name: title
properties.description: • title - (Required, string) A title to describe the deploy key with.

properties.name: key
properties.description: • key - (Required, string) The public ssh key body.

properties.name: can_push
properties.description: • can_push - (Optional, boolean) Allow this deploy key to be used to push changes to the project. Defaults to false. NOTE:: this cannot currently be managed.
The following arguments are supported:

properties.name: project
properties.description: • project - (Required, string) The name or id of the project to add the deploy key to.

properties.name: key_id
properties.description: • key_id - (Required, string) The Gitlab key id for the pre-existing deploy key
The following arguments are supported:

properties.name: name
properties.description: • name - (Required) The name of this group.

properties.name: path
properties.description: • path - (Required) The path of the group.

properties.name: description
properties.description: • description - (Optional) The description of the group.

properties.name: lfs_enabled
properties.description: • lfs_enabled - (Optional) Boolean, defaults to true. Whether to enable LFS support for projects in this group.

properties.name: request_access_enabled
properties.description: • request_access_enabled - (Optional) Boolean, defaults to false. Whether to enable users to request access to the group.

properties.name: visibility_level
properties.description: • visibility_level - (Optional) Set to public to create a public group. Valid values are private, internal, public. Groups are created as private by default.

properties.name: parent_id
properties.description: • parent_id - (Optional) Integer, id of the parent group (creates a nested group).
The following arguments are supported:

properties.name: group_id
properties.description: • group_id - (Required) The id of the group.

properties.name: user_id
properties.description: • user_id - (Required) The id of the user.

properties.name: access_level
properties.description: • access_level - (Required) Acceptable values are: guest, reporter, developer, master, owner.

properties.name: expires_at
properties.description: • expires_at - (Optional) Expiration date for the group membership. Format: YYYY-MM-DD
The following arguments are supported:

properties.name: group
properties.description: • group - (Required, string) The name or id of the group to add the hook to.

properties.name: key
properties.description: • key - (Required, string) The name of the variable.

properties.name: value
properties.description: • value - (Required, string) The value of the variable.

properties.name: variable_type
properties.description: • variable_type - (Optional, string) The type of a variable. Available types are: env_var (default) and file.

properties.name: protected
properties.description: • protected - (Optional, boolean) If set to true, the variable will be passed only to pipelines running on protected branches and tags. Defaults to false.
The following arguments are supported:

properties.name: project
properties.description: • project - (Required) The name or id of the project to add the label to.

properties.name: name
properties.description: • name - (Required) The name of the label.

properties.name: color
properties.description: • color - (Required) The color of the label given in 6-digit hex notation with leading '#' sign (e.g. #FFAABB) or one of the CSS color names.

properties.name: description
properties.description: • description - (Optional) The description of the label.
The following arguments are supported:

properties.name: project
properties.description: • project - (Required, string) The name or id of the project to add the schedule to.

properties.name: description
properties.description: • description - (Required, string) The description of the pipeline schedule.

properties.name: ref
properties.description: • ref - (Required, string) The branch/tag name to be triggered.

properties.name: cron
properties.description: • cron - (Required, string) The cron (e.g. 0 1 * * *).

properties.name: cron_timezone
properties.description: • cron_timezone - (Optional, string) The timezone.

properties.name: active
properties.description: • active - (Optional, bool) The activation of pipeline schedule. If false is set, the pipeline schedule will deactivated initially.
The following arguments are supported:

properties.name: project
properties.description: • project - (Required, string) The name or id of the project to add the trigger to.

properties.name: description
properties.description: • description - (Required, string) The description of the pipeline trigger.
The following arguments are supported:

properties.name: name
properties.description: • name - (Required) The name of the project.

properties.name: path
properties.description: • path - (Optional) The path of the repository.

properties.name: namespace_id
properties.description: • namespace_id - (Optional) The namespace (group or user) of the project. Defaults to your user. See gitlab_group for an example.

properties.name: description
properties.description: • description - (Optional) A description of the project.

properties.name: tags
properties.description: • tags - (Optional) Tags (topics) of the project.

properties.name: default_branch
properties.description: • default_branch - (Optional) The default branch for the project.

properties.name: issues_enabled
properties.description: • issues_enabled - (Optional) Enable issue tracking for the project.

properties.name: merge_requests_enabled
properties.description: • merge_requests_enabled - (Optional) Enable merge requests for the project.

properties.name: approvals_before_merge
properties.description: • approvals_before_merge - (Optional) Number of merge request approvals required for merging. Default is 0.

properties.name: wiki_enabled
properties.description: • wiki_enabled - (Optional) Enable wiki for the project.

properties.name: snippets_enabled
properties.description: • snippets_enabled - (Optional) Enable snippets for the project.

properties.name: container_registry_enabled
properties.description: • container_registry_enabled - (Optional) Enable container registry for the project.

properties.name: visibility_level
properties.description: • visibility_level - (Optional) Set to public to create a public project. Valid values are private, internal, public. Repositories are created as private by default.

properties.name: merge_method
properties.description: • merge_method - (Optional) Set to ff to create fast-forward merges Valid values are merge, rebase_merge, ff Repositories are created with merge by default

properties.name: only_allow_merge_if_pipeline_succeeds
properties.description: • only_allow_merge_if_pipeline_succeeds - (Optional) Set to true if you want allow merges only if a pipeline succeeds.

properties.name: only_allow_merge_if_all_discussions_are_resolved
properties.description: • only_allow_merge_if_all_discussions_are_resolved - (Optional) Set to true if you want allow merges only if all discussions are resolved.

properties.name: shared_runners_enabled
properties.description: • shared_runners_enabled - (Optional) Enable shared runners for this project.

properties.name: list description
properties.description: shared_with_groups - (Optional) Enable sharing the project with a list of groups (maps).

properties.name: group_id
properties.description: (Required) Group id of the group you want to share the project with.

properties.name: group_access_level
properties.description: (Required) Group's sharing permissions. See group members permission for more info. Valid values are guest, reporter, developer, master.

properties.name: archived
properties.description: • archived - (Optional) Whether the project is in read-only mode (archived). Repositories can be archived/unarchived by toggling this parameter.

properties.name: initialize_with_readme
properties.description: • initialize_with_readme - (Optional) Create master branch with first commit containing a README.md file.
The following arguments are supported:

properties.name: project
properties.description: • project - (Required, string) The id of the project to add the cluster to.

properties.name: name
properties.description: • name - (Required, string) The name of cluster.

properties.name: domain
properties.description: • domain - (Optional, string) The base domain of the cluster.

properties.name: enabled
properties.description: • enabled - (Optional, boolean) Determines if cluster is active or not. Defaults to true. This attribute cannot be read.

properties.name: managed
properties.description: • managed - (Optional, boolean) Determines if cluster is managed by gitlab or not. Defaults to true. This attribute cannot be read.

properties.name: kubernetes_api_url
properties.description: • kubernetes_api_url - (Required, string) The URL to access the Kubernetes API.

properties.name: kubernetes_token
properties.description: • kubernetes_token - (Required, string) The token to authenticate against Kubernetes.

properties.name: kubernetes_ca_cert
properties.description: • kubernetes_ca_cert - (Optional, string) TLS certificate (needed if API is using a self-signed TLS certificate).

properties.name: kubernetes_namespace
properties.description: • kubernetes_namespace - (Optional, string) The unique namespace related to the project.

properties.name: kubernetes_authorization_type
properties.description: • kubernetes_authorization_type - (Optional, string) The cluster authorization type. Valid values are rbac, abac, unknown_authorization. Defaults to rbac.

properties.name: environment_scope
properties.description: • environment_scope - (Optional, string) The associated environment to the cluster. Defaults to *.
The following arguments are supported:

properties.name: project
properties.description: • project - (Required) The name or id of the project to add the hook to.

properties.name: url
properties.description: • url - (Required) The url of the hook to invoke.

properties.name: token
properties.description: • token - (Optional) A token to present when invoking the hook.

properties.name: enable_ssl_verification
properties.description: • enable_ssl_verification - (Optional) Enable ssl verification when invoking the hook.

properties.name: push_events
properties.description: • push_events - (Optional) Invoke the hook for push events.

properties.name: issues_events
properties.description: • issues_events - (Optional) Invoke the hook for issues events.

properties.name: merge_requests_events
properties.description: • merge_requests_events - (Optional) Invoke the hook for merge requests.

properties.name: tag_push_events
properties.description: • tag_push_events - (Optional) Invoke the hook for tag push events.

properties.name: note_events
properties.description: • note_events - (Optional) Invoke the hook for notes events.

properties.name: job_events
properties.description: • job_events - (Optional) Invoke the hook for job events.

properties.name: pipeline_events
properties.description: • pipeline_events - (Optional) Invoke the hook for pipeline events.

properties.name: wiki_page_events
properties.description: • wiki_page_events - (Optional) Invoke the hook for wiki page events.
The following arguments are supported:

properties.name: project_id
properties.description: • project_id - (Required) The id of the project.

properties.name: user_id
properties.description: • user_id - (Required) The id of the user.

properties.name: access_level
properties.description: • access_level - (Required) One of five levels of access to the project.
The following arguments are supported:

properties.name: project_id
properties.description: • project_id - (Required) The id of the project.

properties.name: group_id
properties.description: • group_id - (Required) The id of the group.

properties.name: access_level
properties.description: • access_level - (Required) One of five levels of access to the project.
The following arguments are supported:

properties.name: project
properties.description: • project - (Required, string) The name or id of the project to add the push rules to.

properties.name: commit_message_regex
properties.description: • commit_message_regex - (Optional, string) All commit messages must match this regex, e.g. "Fixed \d+..*"

properties.name: deny_delete_tag
properties.description: • deny_delete_tag - (Optional, bool) Deny deleting a tag

properties.name: member_check
properties.description: • member_check - (Optional, bool) Restrict commits by author (email) to existing GitLab users

properties.name: prevent_secrets
properties.description: • prevent_secrets - (Optional, bool) GitLab will reject any files that are likely to contain secrets

properties.name: branch_name_regex
properties.description: • branch_name_regex - (Optional, string) All branch names must match this regex, e.g. "(feature|hotfix)\/*"

properties.name: author_email_regex
properties.description: • author_email_regex - (Optional, string) All commit author emails must match this regex, e.g. "@my-company.com$"

properties.name: file_name_regex
properties.description: • file_name_regex - (Optional, string) All commited filenames must not match this regex, e.g. "(jar|exe)$"

properties.name: max_file_size
properties.description: • max_file_size - (Optional, int) Maximum file size (MB)

properties.name: commit_committer_check
properties.description: • commit_committer_check - (Optional, bool) Users can only push commits to this repository that were committed with one of their own verified emails

properties.name: project

properties.name: value
properties.description: • value - (Required, string) The value of the variable.

The following arguments are supported:

properties.name: project
properties.description: • project - (Required) ID of the project you want to activate integration on.

properties.name: url
properties.description: • url - (Required) The URL to the JIRA project which is being linked to this GitLab project. For example, https://jira.example.com.

properties.name: username
properties.description: • username - (Required) The username of the user created to be used with GitLab/JIRA.

properties.name: password
properties.description: • password - (Required) The password of the user created to be used with GitLab/JIRA.

properties.name: project_key
properties.description: • project_key - (Required) The short identifier for your JIRA project, all uppercase, e.g., PROJ.

properties.name: jira_issue_transition_id
properties.description: • jira_issue_transition_id - (Optional) The ID of a transition that moves issues to a closed state. You can find this number under the JIRA workflow administration (Administration > Issues > Workflows) by selecting View under Operations of the desired workflow of your project. By default, this ID is set to 2.

properties.name: importing-jira-service
properties.description: » Importing Jira service
You can import a service_jira state using terraform import <resource> <project_id>:
$ terraform import gitlab_service_jira.jira 1
The following arguments are supported:

properties.name: project
properties.description: • project - (Required) ID of the project you want to activate integration on.

properties.name: webhook
properties.description: • webhook - (Required) Webhook URL (ex.: https://hooks.slack.com/services/...)

properties.name: username
properties.description: • username - (Optional) Username to use.

properties.name: notify_only_broken_pipelines
properties.description: • notify_only_broken_pipelines - (Optional) Send notifications for broken pipelines.

properties.name: notify_only_default_branch
properties.description: • notify_only_default_branch - (Optional) Send notifications only for the default branch.

properties.name: push_events
properties.description: • push_events - (Optional) Enable notifications for push events.

properties.name: push_channel
properties.description: • push_channel - (Optional) The name of the channel to receive push events notifications.

properties.name: issues_events
properties.description: • issues_events - (Optional) Enable notifications for issues events.

properties.name: issue_channel
properties.description: • issue_channel - (Optional) The name of the channel to receive issue events notifications.

properties.name: confidential_issues_events
properties.description: • confidential_issues_events - (Optional) Enable notifications for confidential issues events.

properties.name: confidential_issue_channel
properties.description: • confidential_issue_channel - (Optional) The name of the channel to receive confidential issue events notifications.

properties.name: merge_requests_events
properties.description: • merge_requests_events - (Optional) Enable notifications for merge requests events.

properties.name: merge_request_channel
properties.description: • merge_request_channel - (Optional) The name of the channel to receive merge request events notifications.

properties.name: tag_push_events
properties.description: • tag_push_events - (Optional) Enable notifications for tag push events.

properties.name: tag_push_channel
properties.description: • tag_push_channel - (Optional) The name of the channel to receive tag push events notifications.

properties.name: note_events
properties.description: • note_events - (Optional) Enable notifications for note events.

properties.name: note_channel
properties.description: • note_channel - (Optional) The name of the channel to receive note events notifications.

properties.name: confidential_note_events
properties.description: • confidential_note_events - (Optional) Enable notifications for confidential note events.

properties.name: pipeline_events
properties.description: • pipeline_events - (Optional) Enable notifications for pipeline events.

properties.name: pipeline_channel
properties.description: • pipeline_channel - (Optional) The name of the channel to receive pipeline events notifications.

properties.name: wiki_page_events
properties.description: • wiki_page_events - (Optional) Enable notifications for wiki page events.

properties.name: wiki_page_channel
properties.description: • wiki_page_channel - (Optional) The name of the channel to receive wiki page events notifications.

properties.name: importing-slack-service
properties.description: » Importing Slack service
You can import a service_slack state using terraform import <resource> <project_id>:
$ terraform import gitlab_service_slack.slack 1
The following arguments are supported:

properties.name: project
properties.description: • project - (Required) The id of the project.

properties.name: tag
properties.description: • tag - (Required) Name of the tag or wildcard.

properties.name: create_access_level
properties.description: • create_access_level - (Required) One of five levels of access to the project.
The following arguments are supported:

properties.name: name
properties.description: • name - (Required) The name of the user.

properties.name: username
properties.description: • username - (Required) The username of the user.

properties.name: password
properties.description: • password - (Required) The password of the user.

properties.name: email
properties.description: • email - (Required) The e-mail address of the user.

properties.name: is_admin
properties.description: • is_admin - (Optional) Boolean, defaults to false. Whether to enable administrative priviledges for the user.

properties.name: projects_limit
properties.description: • projects_limit - (Optional) Integer, defaults to 0. Number of projects user can create.

properties.name: can_create_group
properties.description: • can_create_group - (Optional) Boolean, defaults to false. Whether to allow the user to create groups.

properties.name: skip_confirmation
properties.description: • skip_confirmation - (Optional) Boolean, defaults to true. Whether to skip confirmation.

properties.name: is_external
properties.description: • is_external - (Optional) Boolean, defaults to false. Whether a user has access only to some internal or private projects. External users can only access projects to which they are explicitly granted access.
